prvtQosMIB.name: prvtQosMIB

revisions.description: Added support for QOS over VLAN.
Changed hqosVirtualSchedulerParent to type TNamedItemOrEmpty. Added some TCs. Miscellaneous additional clean up.

prvtQosMIB.contactinfo: BATM/Telco Systems Support team Email: For North America: techsupport@telco.com For North Europe: support@batm.de, info@batm.de For the rest of the world: techsupport@telco.com
prvtQosMIB.description: This document is the SNMP MIB module to manage the QoS parameters.

TNamedItem.name: TNamedItem
TNamedItem.description: The name of an item. Note, use only NVT ASCII displayable characters here, no control characters, no UTF-8, etc.

TNamedItemOrEmpty.name: TNamedItemOrEmpty
TNamedItemOrEmpty.description: The name of an item, or an empty string. When used in a reference (TNamedItemOrEmpty) the item name entry must exist in the table. Note, use only NVT ASCII displayable characters here, no control characters, no UTF-8, etc.

TQEncapVal.name: TQEncapVal
TQEncapVal.description: A valid Vlan ID in the range 1-4093, or 65535.

TLspExpValue.name: TLspExpValue
TLspExpValue.description: MPLS Experimental bits. -1 means not set.

Dot1PPriority.name: Dot1PPriority
Dot1PPriority.description: IEEE 802.1p priority. zero is lowest, seven is highest. -1 means not set

TFCName.name: TFCName
TFCName.description: The name of a Forwarding Class entry.

TFCNameOrEmpty.name: TFCNameOrEmpty
TFCNameOrEmpty.description: The name of a Forwarding Class entry.

TDSCPValue.name: TDSCPValue
TDSCPValue.description: The value of a Differential Services Code Point.

TItemDescription.name: TItemDescription
TItemDescription.description: Description for an item. Note, use only NVT ASCII displayable characters here, no control characters, no UTF-8, etc.

TQueueId.name: TQueueId
TQueueId.description: The identification number of a queue. zero means not set. legal values when used for an index are [1..32].

TIngressQueueId.name: TIngressQueueId
TIngressQueueId.description: The identification number of a queue. zero means not set. legal values when used for an index are [1..32].

TEgressQueueId.name: TEgressQueueId
TEgressQueueId.description: The identification number of an egress queue. zero means not set. legal values when used for an index are [1..32].

TSapIngressPolicyId.name: TSapIngressPolicyId
TSapIngressPolicyId.description: The identification number of a SAP ingress policy.

TSapIngressPolicyIdOrNone.name: TSapIngressPolicyIdOrNone
TSapIngressPolicyIdOrNone.description: The identification number of a SAP ingress policy. A value of 0 indicates no policy.

TSapEgressPolicyId.name: TSapEgressPolicyId
TSapEgressPolicyId.description: The identification number of a SAP egress policy.

TSapEgressPolicyIdOrNone.name: TSapEgressPolicyIdOrNone
TSapEgressPolicyIdOrNone.description: The identification number of a SAP egress policy. A value of 0 indicates no policy.

TNetworkPolicyId.name: TNetworkPolicyId
TNetworkPolicyId.description: The identification string of a network policy.

TNetworkPolicyIdOrNone.name: TNetworkPolicyIdOrNone
TNetworkPolicyIdOrNone.description: The identification string of a network policy.

TItemMatch.name: TItemMatch
TItemMatch.description: When set to off, the item is not matched. When set to false, packets without the item match the filter. When set to true, packets with the item match the filter.

TPriority.name: TPriority
TPriority.description: The priority to apply to a packet

TPriorityOrDefault.name: TPriorityOrDefault
TPriorityOrDefault.description: The priority to apply to a packet. When set to default(3), the priority from the default-action is used.

TProfile.name: TProfile
TProfile.description: The profile marking of a packet at the ingress.

TCIRRate.name: TCIRRate
TCIRRate.description: The rate to be used in kbps.

TPIRRate.name: TPIRRate
TPIRRate.description: The rate to be used in kbps.

TRateValue.name: TRateValue
TRateValue.description: The percentage of maximum rate allowed.

TLevel.name: TLevel
TLevel.description: The level of the specified entity while feeding into the parent.

TWeight.name: TWeight
TWeight.description: The weight of the specified entity while feeding into the parent.

TTreshold.name: TTreshold
TTreshold.description: The treshold to be used in %.Valid values are 25, 50, 75, 100%.

TConformanceLevel.name: TConformanceLevel
TConformanceLevel.description: The conformance level green or yellow.

TShaperId.name: TShaperId
TShaperId.description: The ID of a Shaper Profile.

TTailDropId.name: TTailDropId
TTailDropId.description: The ID of a TailDrop Profile.

TSredId.name: TSredId
TSredId.description: The ID of a SRED Profile.

TSSchedulingProfile.name: TSSchedulingProfile
TSSchedulingProfile.description: The ID of a Scheduling Profile.

TSlopePolicy.name: TSlopePolicy
TSlopePolicy.description: The ID of a Wred Profile.

tFCNameTable.name: tFCNameTable
tFCNameTable.description: A list of all Forwarding Class Names. Forwarding Class Name entries must exist here and be active before they can be referenced elsewhere (e.g. qos queue).

tFCNameEntry.name: tFCNameEntry
tFCNameEntry.description: Information about a particular Forwarding Class Name, particularly the Forwarding Class value. Some default entries are created by the agent. Default entries have tFCNameStorageType permanent, and can not be deleted. Entries cannot be created by user but maybe supported in future. An attempt to create a row in this table would return no creation.

tFCValue.name: tFCValue
tFCValue.description: Forwarding class number as used in the tables below.

tFCStorageType.name: tFCStorageType
tFCStorageType.description: The storage type of this row in the table.

tFCNameLastChanged.name: tFCNameLastChanged
tFCNameLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in tFCNameTable.

hqosSapIngressTable.name: hqosSapIngressTable
hqosSapIngressTable.description: This table specifies HQoS service ingress policy configuration.

hqosSapIngressEntry.name: hqosSapIngressEntry
hqosSapIngressEntry.description: Information about a particular HQoS Sap Ingress Policy. sap-ingress policy (1) is the default entry. Default Entry is created by the agent, other entries are created by user. Default Entry cannot be modified/deleted. The other entries are deleted by user. There is no StorageType object, entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile.

hqosSapIngressIndex.name: hqosSapIngressIndex
hqosSapIngressIndex.description: The identifier of a HQoS service ingress policy. The policy ID is the index to this table.

hqosSapIngressRowStatus.name: hqosSapIngressRowStatus
hqosSapIngressRowStatus.description: Row Status for the policy. The deletion of this row has an action of removing the dependent rows in the following tables : - hqosSapIngressQueueTable - hqosSapIngressDSCPTable - hqosSapIngressDot1pTable

hqosSapIngressDefaultDscpFC.name: hqosSapIngressDefaultDscpFC
hqosSapIngressDefaultDscpFC.description: All traffic that does not match the specified dot1p, DSCP, is classified as the default action forwarding class. The default forwarding class is best-effort.

hqosSapIngressDefaultVptFC.name: hqosSapIngressDefaultVptFC
hqosSapIngressDefaultVptFC.description: The priority to assign to traffic ingressing as the default action queue.

hqosSapIngressLastChanged.name: hqosSapIngressLastChanged
hqosSapIngressLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in tSapIngressTable.

hqosSapIngressQueueTable.name: hqosSapIngressQueueTable
hqosSapIngressQueueTable.description: Information about all HQoS service ingress policies' queues.

hqosSapIngressQueueEntry.name: hqosSapIngressQueueEntry
hqosSapIngressQueueEntry.description: Information about a particular queue for a service ingress policy. Some default queues are created by the system, they cannot be removed. Other entries are created by user.

hqosSapIngressQueue.name: hqosSapIngressQueue
hqosSapIngressQueue.description: The queue ID is used as the secondary index to the table entry.

hqosSapIngressQueueParent.name: hqosSapIngressQueueParent
hqosSapIngressQueueParent.description: The scheduler to which this queue would be feeding to.

hqosSapIngressQueueRowStatus.name: hqosSapIngressQueueRowStatus
hqosSapIngressQueueRowStatus.description: Row Status of the entry. This allows creation/deletion of rows in this table.

hqosSapIngressQueueLevel.name: hqosSapIngressQueueLevel
hqosSapIngressQueueLevel.description: This specifies the level of priority while feeding to the parent.

hqosSapIngressQueueServWfq.name: hqosSapIngressQueueServWfq
hqosSapIngressQueueServWfq.description: The WFQ profile that needs to be used by the scheduler to which this queue would be feeding to.

hqosSapIngressQueueType.name: hqosSapIngressQueueType
hqosSapIngressQueueType.description: This object specifies the traffic type of the queue.

hqosSapIngressQueueWred.name: hqosSapIngressQueueWred
hqosSapIngressQueueWred.description: WRED profile applied to this queue.

hqosSapIngressQueueLastChanged.name: hqosSapIngressQueueLastChanged
hqosSapIngressQueueLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in hqosSapIngressQueueTable.

hqosSapIngressDSCPTable.name: hqosSapIngressDSCPTable
hqosSapIngressDSCPTable.description: A list of all DSCP entries for service ingress policies.

hqosSapIngressDSCPEntry.name: hqosSapIngressDSCPEntry
hqosSapIngressDSCPEntry.description: Information about a particular DSCP entry for a service ingress policy. Entries are created by user. Entries are deleted by user. There is no StorageType object, entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile. In the event that one policy has multiple entries, and the hqosSapIngressDSCP values are the same, only one queue will be created (the queue for the lexicographically first hqosSapIngressDSCP).

hqosSapIngressDSCP.name: hqosSapIngressDSCP
hqosSapIngressDSCP.description: Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) value as to match in the packet. This value is also used index so that for any DSCP value there is only one possible disposition queue and priority.

hqosSapIngressDSCPRowStatus.name: hqosSapIngressDSCPRowStatus
hqosSapIngressDSCPRowStatus.description: This object allows creation/deletion of rows in this table.

hqosSapIngressDSCPFC.name: hqosSapIngressDSCPFC
hqosSapIngressDSCPFC.description: The forwarding class into which the matching traffic should be classified.

hqosSapIngressDSCPConformance.name: hqosSapIngressDSCPConformance
hqosSapIngressDSCPConformance.description: Previous conformance level: green or yellow.

hqosSapIngressDSCPLastChanged.name: hqosSapIngressDSCPLastChanged
hqosSapIngressDSCPLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in hqosSapIngressDSCPTable.

hqosSapIngressDot1pTable.name: hqosSapIngressDot1pTable
hqosSapIngressDot1pTable.description: A list of all dot1p entries for service ingress policies.

hqosSapIngressDot1pEntry.name: hqosSapIngressDot1pEntry
hqosSapIngressDot1pEntry.description: Information about a particular dot1p match for a service ingress policy. Entries are created by user. Entries are deleted by user.

hqosSapIngressDot1pValue.name: hqosSapIngressDot1pValue
hqosSapIngressDot1pValue.description: Dot1p value to match in the packet. This value is also used as an index so that for any dot1p value there is only one possible disposition queue and priority.

hqosSapIngressDot1pRowStatus.name: hqosSapIngressDot1pRowStatus
hqosSapIngressDot1pRowStatus.description: Row Status for this service ingress policy's dot1p entry.

hqosSapIngressDot1pFC.name: hqosSapIngressDot1pFC
hqosSapIngressDot1pFC.description: The forwarding class into which the matching traffic should be classified.

hqosSapIngressDot1pConformance.name: hqosSapIngressDot1pConformance
hqosSapIngressDot1pConformance.description: Previous conformance level: green or yellow

hqosSapIngressDot1pLastChanged.name: hqosSapIngressDot1pLastChanged
hqosSapIngressDot1pLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in hqosSapIngressDot1pTable.

hqosSapIngressFCTable.name: hqosSapIngressFCTable
hqosSapIngressFCTable.description: This table maintains the mapping of a particular forwarding class traffic into the specified queue.

hqosSapIngressFCEntry.name: hqosSapIngressFCEntry
hqosSapIngressFCEntry.description: Information about a particular service ingress policy's forwarding class mappings to queues. Entries are created and deleted by user.

hqosSapIngressFCQueueType.name: hqosSapIngressFCQueueType
hqosSapIngressFCQueueType.description: The type of the queue to be assigned to the FC.

hqosSapIngressFCQueue.name: hqosSapIngressFCQueue
hqosSapIngressFCQueue.description: The specific queue to be used for packets in this forwarding class.

hqosSapIngressFCQueueParent.name: hqosSapIngressFCQueueParent
hqosSapIngressFCQueueParent.description: The parent of the specific queue for this FC

hqosSapIngressFCLastChanged.name: hqosSapIngressFCLastChanged
hqosSapIngressFCLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in hqosSapIngressFCTable.

hqosSapEgressTable.name: hqosSapEgressTable
hqosSapEgressTable.description: Information about all service egress policies.

hqosSapEgressEntry.name: hqosSapEgressEntry
hqosSapEgressEntry.description: Information about a particular service egress policy. Entries are created by user. Entries are deleted by user. The default service egress policy (1) cannot be changed or destroyed.

hqosSapEgressIndex.name: hqosSapEgressIndex
hqosSapEgressIndex.description: The service egress policy ID is used as index for the table.

hqosSapEgressRowStatus.name: hqosSapEgressRowStatus
hqosSapEgressRowStatus.description: Row Status of this policy's entry.

hqosSapEgressDescription.name: hqosSapEgressDescription
hqosSapEgressDescription.description: User-supplied description of this service egress policy.

hqosSapEgressLastChanged.name: hqosSapEgressLastChanged
hqosSapEgressLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in hqosSapEgressTable.

hqosSapEgressQueueTable.name: hqosSapEgressQueueTable
hqosSapEgressQueueTable.description: Information about service egress policies' queues.

hqosSapEgressQueueEntry.name: hqosSapEgressQueueEntry
hqosSapEgressQueueEntry.description: Information about a particular service egress queue. Entries are created by user. Entries are deleted by user.

hqosSapEgressQueueIndex.name: hqosSapEgressQueueIndex
hqosSapEgressQueueIndex.description: The number of a queue.Zero is not allowed.

hqosSapEgressQueueParent.name: hqosSapEgressQueueParent
hqosSapEgressQueueParent.description: The scheduler to which this queue would be feeding to.

hqosSapEgressQueueLevel.name: hqosSapEgressQueueLevel
hqosSapEgressQueueLevel.description: This specifies the level of priority while feeding to the parent.

hqosSapEgressQueueServWfq.name: hqosSapEgressQueueServWfq
hqosSapEgressQueueServWfq.description: The WFQ profile that needs to be used by the scheduler to which this queue would be feeding to.

hqosSapEgressQueueType.name: hqosSapEgressQueueType
hqosSapEgressQueueType.description: This object specifies the traffic type of the queue.

hqosSapEgressQueueWred.name: hqosSapEgressQueueWred
hqosSapEgressQueueWred.description: ID of WRED profile applied to this queue.

hqosSapEgressQueueLastChanged.name: hqosSapEgressQueueLastChanged
hqosSapEgressQueueLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in hqosSapEgressQueueTable.

hqosSapEgressFCTable.name: hqosSapEgressFCTable
hqosSapEgressFCTable.description: Information about a particular service egress policy's forwarding class mappings to queues. Entries are created and deleted by user.

hqosSapEgressFCEntry.name: hqosSapEgressFCEntry
hqosSapEgressFCEntry.description: Information about a particular service egress policy's forwarding class mappings to queues and dot1p values. Entries are created by user. Entries are deleted by user.

hqosSapEgressFCEntryType.name: hqosSapEgressFCEntryType
hqosSapEgressFCEntryType.description: The type of the configuration entry for this FC.

hqosSapEgressFCQueue.name: hqosSapEgressFCQueue
hqosSapEgressFCQueue.description: The queue to use for packets with this forwarding class. A valid queue-id must be specified before setting the row status to active.

hqosSapEgressFCQueueParent.name: hqosSapEgressFCQueueParent
hqosSapEgressFCQueueParent.description: The name of the parent scheduler for the specific queue.

hqosSapEgressFCDot1PValue.name: hqosSapEgressFCDot1PValue
hqosSapEgressFCDot1PValue.description: The 802.1p value to use for packet remarking.Currently not supported.

hqosSapEgressFCDSCPValue.name: hqosSapEgressFCDSCPValue
hqosSapEgressFCDSCPValue.description: The DSCP value to use for packets remarking. Currently not supported.

hqosSapEgressFCLastChanged.name: hqosSapEgressFCLastChanged
hqosSapEgressFCLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in hqosSapEgressFCTable.

hqosNetworkPolicyTable.name: hqosNetworkPolicyTable
hqosNetworkPolicyTable.description: HQOS network policy table. Keeps comman information of the network policy

hqosNetworkPolicyEntry.name: hqosNetworkPolicyEntry
hqosNetworkPolicyEntry.description: Information about a particular Network Policy. Network policy DefPol(1) is the default entry. Default Entry is created by the agent, other entries are created by user. Default Entry cannot be modified/deleted. The other entries are deleted by user. There is no StorageType object, entries have a presumed StorageType of nonVolatile. The default Egress FC entries are created as an action of setting the rowstatus.

hqosNetworkPolicyRowStatus.name: hqosNetworkPolicyRowStatus
hqosNetworkPolicyRowStatus.description: Row status of the network policy HQoS network policy is created with createAndWait(5).

hqosNetworkPolicyDescription.name: hqosNetworkPolicyDescription
hqosNetworkPolicyDescription.description: User-defined description of the network policy

hqosNetworkPolicyIngressDefaultActionFC.name: hqosNetworkPolicyIngressDefaultActionFC
hqosNetworkPolicyIngressDefaultActionFC.description: Network policy default action FC. Currently not used. Reserved for future use.

hqosNetworkPolicyIngressConformance.name: hqosNetworkPolicyIngressConformance
hqosNetworkPolicyIngressConformance.description: Defines network conformance level green or yellow. Currently not used. Reserved for future use.

hqosNetworkPolicyEgressRemark.name: hqosNetworkPolicyEgressRemark
hqosNetworkPolicyEgressRemark.description: Verifies if remarking is set on network egress. Remarking is enabled by default

hqosNetworkPolicyLastChanged.name: hqosNetworkPolicyLastChanged
hqosNetworkPolicyLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in hqosNetworkPolicyTable.

hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPTable.name: hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPTable
hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPTable.description: Information about network ingress policies' mappings.

hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPEntry.name: hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPEntry
hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPEntry.description: Information about LSP EXP mapping for a network policy. Some default entries are created by the agent for the default network policy DefPol(1). These cannot be deleted or modified. Other entries are created/deleted by user.

hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPRowStatus.name: hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPRowStatus
hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPRowStatus.description: Row status of network ingress mapping

hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPFC.name: hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPFC
hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPFC.description: Mapping of LSP EXP to forwarding class.

hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPConformance.name: hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPConformance
hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPConformance.description: Indentifies conformance level green or yellow for a frame with a LSP EXP bit value.

hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPLastChanged.name: hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPLastChanged
hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in hqosNetworkIngressLSPEXPTable. Currently not supported

hqosNetworkEgressFCTable.name: hqosNetworkEgressFCTable
hqosNetworkEgressFCTable.description: Information about all network policies' egress FC traffic disposition.

hqosNetworkEgressFCEntry.name: hqosNetworkEgressFCEntry
hqosNetworkEgressFCEntry.description: Information about a particular network policy's egress per-forwarding-class traffic disposition. Entries are created/deleted as an action of creating/deleting a row in the hqosNetworkPolicyTable.

hqosNetworkEgressFCNumber.name: hqosNetworkEgressFCNumber
hqosNetworkEgressFCNumber.description: The number of the forwarding class (FC).

hqosNetworkEgressFCRowStatus.name: hqosNetworkEgressFCRowStatus
hqosNetworkEgressFCRowStatus.description: The row status of this row. Only the value of createAndWait(5) is available for row creation

hqosNetworkEgressFCLspExpValue.name: hqosNetworkEgressFCLspExpValue
hqosNetworkEgressFCLspExpValue.description: Network egress remarking value for LSP EXP bits.

hqosNetworkEgressFCDot1Priority.name: hqosNetworkEgressFCDot1Priority
hqosNetworkEgressFCDot1Priority.description: Network egress remarking value for Dot1p. Currently not supported. Reserved for future use.

hqosNetworkEgressFCLastChanged.name: hqosNetworkEgressFCLastChanged
hqosNetworkEgressFCLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in hqosNetworkEgressFCTable.

hqosNetworkQueuePolicyEntry.name: hqosNetworkQueuePolicyEntry
hqosNetworkQueuePolicyEntry.description: Information about network egress queue configuration

hqosNetworkQueuePolicy.name: hqosNetworkQueuePolicy
hqosNetworkQueuePolicy.description: Name of network egress queue policy. This is the index in the table. Should be no more than 6 characters long.

hqosNetworkQueuePolicyRowStatus.name: hqosNetworkQueuePolicyRowStatus
hqosNetworkQueuePolicyRowStatus.description: The row status. Used for creation of a row in the table.

hqosNetworkQueuePolicyDescription.name: hqosNetworkQueuePolicyDescription
hqosNetworkQueuePolicyDescription.description: User-defined description of the network policy.

hqosNetworkQueuePolicyLastChanged.name: hqosNetworkQueuePolicyLastChanged
hqosNetworkQueuePolicyLastChanged.description: The time when an object in the row was last changed. Currently not supported.

hqosNetworkQueue.name: hqosNetworkQueue
hqosNetworkQueue.description: Network queue identifier. The queue ID is used as an index of the table entry.

hqosNetworkQueueRowStatus.name: hqosNetworkQueueRowStatus
hqosNetworkQueueRowStatus.description: Row Status of the entry. This allows creation/deletion of rows in this table.

hqosNetworkQueueParent.name: hqosNetworkQueueParent
hqosNetworkQueueParent.description: Network queue parent is not configurable. Reserved for future use.

hqosNetworkQueueLevel.name: hqosNetworkQueueLevel
hqosNetworkQueueLevel.description: This specifies the level of priority while feeding to the parent. Priority levels are high(1) or low(2)

hqosNetworkQueueWfqProfile.name: hqosNetworkQueueWfqProfile
hqosNetworkQueueWfqProfile.description: The WFQ profile for this network queue

hqosNetworkQueueType.name: hqosNetworkQueueType
hqosNetworkQueueType.description: This object specifies the type of the network queue. The possible values are: - unknown(0) - unicast(1) - multicast(2) - broadcast(3)

hqosNetworkQueueHiPriority.name: hqosNetworkQueueHiPriority
hqosNetworkQueueHiPriority.description: The object specifies is this a high-priority queue. This object is obsolete, use object hqosNetworkQueueLevel instead

hqosNetworkQueueWred.name: hqosNetworkQueueWred
hqosNetworkQueueWred.description: ID of WRED profile applied to this queue.

hqosNetworkQueueShaper.name: hqosNetworkQueueShaper
hqosNetworkQueueShaper.description: ID of shaping profile applied to this queue. There is no default value

hqosNetworkQueueLastChanged.name: hqosNetworkQueueLastChanged
hqosNetworkQueueLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in hqosNetworkQueueTable. Not supported. Reserved for future use.

hqosNetworkQueueFCTable.name: hqosNetworkQueueFCTable
hqosNetworkQueueFCTable.description: Information which network egress queue traffic with a FC assigned on ingress feeds to.

hqosNetworkQueueFCEntry.name: hqosNetworkQueueFCEntry
hqosNetworkQueueFCEntry.description: Forwarding class to network queue configuratiom

hqosNetworkQueueFCNumber.name: hqosNetworkQueueFCNumber
hqosNetworkQueueFCNumber.description: The number of the forwarding class as referenced in the tFCNameTable.

hqosNetworkQueueFCType.name: hqosNetworkQueueFCType
hqosNetworkQueueFCType.description: The type of the queue to be assigned to the forwarding class. The possible values of this object are: - unknown(0) - unicast(1) - multicast(2) - broadcast(3) This object is part of the index.

hqosNetworkQueueFCRowStatus.name: hqosNetworkQueueFCRowStatus
hqosNetworkQueueFCRowStatus.description: Row Status for this queue. The object serves to create entries in the table.

hqosNetworkQueueFC.name: hqosNetworkQueueFC
hqosNetworkQueueFC.description: The queue id to be mapped.

hqosNetworkQueueFCLastChanged.name: hqosNetworkQueueFCLastChanged
hqosNetworkQueueFCLastChanged.description: The time when an object in the row was last changed.

hqosSchedulerPolicyTable.name: hqosSchedulerPolicyTable
hqosSchedulerPolicyTable.description: Information about a service scheduler policy.

hqosSchedulerPolicyEntry.name: hqosSchedulerPolicyEntry
hqosSchedulerPolicyEntry.description: Information about a particular service scheduler policy.

hqosSchedulerPolicyName.name: hqosSchedulerPolicyName
hqosSchedulerPolicyName.description: This is the index of the table. Should be no more that 6 characters long.

hqosSchedulerPolicyRowStatus.name: hqosSchedulerPolicyRowStatus
hqosSchedulerPolicyRowStatus.description: Row Status of the entry. The entry in the table that serves to create rows.

hqosSchedulerPolicyType.name: hqosSchedulerPolicyType
hqosSchedulerPolicyType.description: Type of the scheduler - ingress or egress. The object can accept one of the three values: - unknown(0) - ingress(1) - egress (2) The value unknown is the default one, but causes the row to be in notReady(3) state. network (3) is not supported

hqosSchedulerPolicyLastChanged.name: hqosSchedulerPolicyLastChanged
hqosSchedulerPolicyLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this row in hqosSchedulerPolicyTable. Reserved for future use.

hqosVirtualSchedulerTable.name: hqosVirtualSchedulerTable
hqosVirtualSchedulerTable.description: Information about schedulers belonging to scheduler policies

hqosVirtualSchedulerEntry.name: hqosVirtualSchedulerEntry
hqosVirtualSchedulerEntry.description: Information about a particular Scheduler belonging to a Scheduler Policy.

hqosVirtualSchedulerRowStatus.name: hqosVirtualSchedulerRowStatus
hqosVirtualSchedulerRowStatus.description: Row Status of the entry. Part of the index together with the policy name and the tier. Should be up to 6 characters long.

hqosVirtualSchedulerDescription.name: hqosVirtualSchedulerDescription
